The Chronicle Sikhumbuzo Moyo, Senior Reporter MenBelievED, a group of empowered men who are rallying behind the Presidency of Cde Mnangagwa by telling the world in general and Zimbabwe in particular about the achievements already done by his administration and the vision that he has for the country in line with his mantra, ilizwe lakhiwa ngabanikazi balo, is one of the first-time exhibitors at the ZITF. <img class="size-full wp-image-598962" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/FDGG.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/FDGG.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/FDGG-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> President Mnangagwa MenbelievED, founded by Justin Matsatsira and launched this year by Cde Mnangagwa who is the patron, says it is committed to telling the true story of Zimbabwe as opposed to what is being done by some social media and a section of the mainstream media spin doctors that seem to never see nor hear anything good done by the Second Republic. menbelieved is a group of empowered men who are rallying behind his Excellency Cde Mnangagwa and also heralding to the world in general and Zimbabwe in particular about the achievements done by him and the vision that he has for this country, following on his mantra that Ilizwe lakhiwa ngabanikazi balo. “We believe we are sons of this soil and also, it’s our responsibility to build this country together with him through his visionary leadership as we march towards Vision 2030. We are not activists, nor are we a political party, but an independent organisation that has said we are behind the President because we believe he has delivered what he promised before becoming the Head of State and Government. <img class="size-full wp-image-419021" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/10/Gwayi-Shangani-Dam1.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="379" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/10/Gwayi-Shangani-Dam1.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2018/10/Gwayi-Shangani-Dam1-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Gwayi-Shangani Dam “He promised roads, dams, and all have been delivered, we have the Gwayi-Shangani Dam that had almost stalled under the previous regime, most of our highways there is a signature performance by him. To add to that he has taken over several hundreds of kilometres from City Councils that have been failing to rehabilitate their roads,” said board member and national spokesperson Timothy Nyakudzuka. He said their stand has been a hive of activity with visitors mainly inquiring about how they can join the organisation and help in telling the correct and true Zimbabwean story having realised the untruths from various social media platforms as well as sections of the mainstream media.  “Interestingly we have received a lot of inquiries on how one can become a member of the organisation, people have realised that social and mainstream media sometimes lie a lot, they portray a wrong picture about the new dispensation. We are encouraging people to participate in this great movement where we tell the true story about Zimbabwe,” he added.